You blew me away last night! Thank you for setting that alarm, showing up, & shopping on your Friday night. Your support is everything 🥹 I had some questions about why I don’t take preorders & just want to explain that a bit. 

First, everything I sell is 100% handmade by my 2 hands (besides my Mom’s heart bowls ☺️) Because of the handmade nature, there are little quirks to each piece. Maybe the 'r' is a little tilted. Maybe the wood grain is different from the last one, or the heart cutout is a different shape, etc. My pieces are premade so you know *exactly* what you’re getting. It also allows me to ship them to you faster! There’s nothing better than placing an order & having something show up a few days later, exactly as it looked online.

Second, I take custom orders for my mini hearts, but I set a limit on how many I take at one time. This allows me to get them out to you in a timely manner, control my workflow, & start on another batch of items for a future restock.

Last thing, did you know I have a chronic illness (POTS)? It’s actually the reason why I started Soulmade Goods! This illness causes my body extreme fatigue, & I have to be careful to not overdo it, or I will be out for days. I love creating so much & am proud to have increased my workload over the last year. I’m working on continuing this upward trend!

I hope this explains things a bit! Please know, I am always trying my best & am just so grateful that you are here, seeing the value in my creations. Thank you for your continued support 💕
